main event: A bright, round object was observed hovering and moving in the night sky over Redwood City, California on February 8, 1967.
interesting points: The object was brighter than the stars and appeared to be self-luminous.
It moved at a high rate of speed and varied in speed, but did not make any sudden maneuvers.
The object was observed for about 3 minutes before disappearing behind trees.
Other witnesses in the area also reported seeing similar objects.
The object did not make any sound and left no visible trail.
